            <h1>Research</h1>
            <div class="temaMobIngressImg" style="display: none;"><img src="/upload/KD/Temabilder/Forskning/forskning1.jpg" alt="" /></div>
            <p class="textIngress">Research is of decisive importance when it comes to ensuring that Norway is a knowledge-based and innovative society. Culture, business and industry and welfare all depend on development and use of research.  </p>
            <img src="/upload/KD/Temabilder/Forskning/forskning1.jpg" alt="" class="temaIngressImg" />
            <div class="descriptionText"><p>Research challenges established perceptions and is necessary if we are to be able to take a stance on new phenomena. Furthermore, research is a pre-requisite for an open and critical social debate and helps us understand ourselves and our surroundings better. New knowledge is a spur to new value creation and innovation. Research strengthens the competitive power of business and industry and is a source of economic growth. Research-based knowledge is becoming increasingly important for solving the challenges that the welfare society is facing in areas such as health, working life and the environment.</p></div>
	    <div style="clear:both"></div>
	      
         </div>
         
         
                                
        
        
        
                            
    <div id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_divPageContent" class="documentBody">  
                

<div class="ArticleView">
        <img src="/upload/KD/Ingressbilder/Forskningsbilder/forsidebilde_forskning_100.jpg" alt="" class="ArticleImg" />
        
        
        <div class="ArticleImgContent">
            <h2><a href="/en/dep/kd/Documents/Brochures-and-handbooks/2009/white-paper-climate-for-research.html?id=557495">Factsheet: White paper on Research</a></h2>        
                
            <p>
               The Government will systematically commit to research in the years to come and will contribute to an increased focus on research results and what our society wants to achieve with our research spending. A one-sided debate on funding and goals for this funding does not aid Norwegian research. There is a definite need for the creation of clear cut policy goals within prioritized areas.
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    
    

    
