                        The oldest complete fossil of a primate
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[19.05.2009]</p>
                <p>An international research team organized by the University of Oslo has for the last two years, in  secret, studied and documented the oldest complete fossil of a primate. The Norwegian government will contribute to the work undertaken by The natural history Museum in Oslo regarding this exceptional fossil by allocating 350 000 dollars to the museum.</p>
                
                
